Notebook[{
Cell["Euclidean Geometry", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"2cf2854e-bf32-4482-a798-f07c88ffdfd1"],

Cell["[LLM Generated]", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"13e539bb-63a2-49bc-9ab9-18ac029936f2"],

Cell["\<\
The Euclidean layer reconstructs the classical primitives \[LongDash] point, \
segment, line, ray, shell, circle, midpoint, perpendicular, parallel, \
bisector \[LongDash] as graph properties under the infra-observer's \
standpoint. Every constructor returns a wrapped Infra* multi-realisation; \
every predicate tests the corresponding pattern.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c78ea2a7-b992-49c9-baf0-65227cb9bac4"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6205df02-e559-4afe-acf1-7a6c6e2eeba3"],

Cell["Load the paclet.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"546de1d6-7fa9-4c46-9143-1c8ea1e4024e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\>\"", 
  "]"}]], "Code",
 InitializationCell->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"bdad87ff-fe11-4f70-9dcd-befbe86a57f8"],

Cell["Primitive postulates", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"aefbc6f9-b3bf-488f-b2f9-5d34c6ae69d4"],

Cell["\<\
Existence postulates following the strict / soft / exhaustive triple \
n_Integer | UpTo[n] | All.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"43d7b454-434f-412c-bb77-58fe1d95977c"],

Cell["FindPoint", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"05970af8-d65b-45bf-94a3-a9cb22aa12b3"],

Cell["FindSegment", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e133bc59-8d91-4fa3-8659-9831846b56d1"],

Cell["FindLine", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5b8c4bbd-6f7a-4b27-b162-81d85c8d366a"],

Cell["FindRay", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e669dd28-f96f-4078-9a38-1b5dfd6c99c3"],

Cell["ExtendSegment", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"aa9406ee-8e6d-4033-8f93-fb089e23cb9c"],

Cell["FindShell", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0a5e2b6a-a069-4433-b5ef-8e1d0a216ebe"],

Cell["FindCircle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"50282100-de77-4b3a-a10d-c04814363759"],

Cell["FindParallel", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8d4f8edd-e1ce-44fd-ab27-5160716699bf"],

Cell["FindBisectingHyperplane", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"df0962e2-f808-48e5-a7a4-30c26612de96"],

Cell["Constructions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"aa3ac70a-e8c1-4a9d-802a-c8c77339a834"],

Cell["FindMidpoint", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3b4b23a8-fa07-4172-85ef-e2420ed18d16"],

Cell["FindPerpendicular", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"6f32df2f-ef08-4e9f-93f6-e26a13d9546a"],

Cell["FindReflection", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0ffdd290-d6fd-423d-b73f-64b874ee0eb8"],

Cell["CompleteEquilateralTriangle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"6f8182d5-a4dc-4e2e-ae77-36ae9fb9ca5a"],

Cell["InfraAngle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f700ba16-8474-4c88-b0eb-7b9fc3781330"],

Cell["SegmentLineAngle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"bc8ab91e-6ea2-434b-9ccb-9b12078be3b1"],

Cell["Predicates", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"58f338bf-77f4-401c-bafa-a753a9ec67a0"],

Cell["SegmentQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"75d4be00-dfc4-4191-8e54-5ef39a0f9864"],

Cell["UniqueSegmentQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"aac6c812-16e7-4d8f-a373-a13fc10e1698"],

Cell["LineQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a2a5cb63-def4-4e8d-80a4-42b9b7199fed"],

Cell["ParallelQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3405d9c6-a364-410b-8ef8-fbce9353de19"],

Cell["ShellQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3ff0af08-3e4a-4b5a-a554-13b7ba2da778"],

Cell["FindShellParameters", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"cd7da929-8eec-417a-9dc8-52909499a8dc"],

Cell["SeparatesQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9c002fe0-9beb-4416-bbde-69106dc930ff"],

Cell["CircleQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a8f3374e-886f-4d20-b6a1-090169db8137"],

Cell["Wrapper heads", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"73e270df-0c78-4e4a-8aff-028d946e21b0"],

Cell["\<\
Every Find* returns a List of unary wrappers; wrapping that List with the \
head collapses to the multi form via auto-flatten.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bf83bef2-f609-4945-9e02-f7ce6c5967f9"],

Cell["InfraPoint", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"aeed309f-8dc8-4e0a-878d-ef1afa5b63a8"],

Cell["InfraSegment", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d2a82d85-52ec-42dd-ac6b-dfcbca3a4372"],

Cell["InfraRay", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"16dbc22a-fb83-4153-b4f8-9138b8c1413c"],

Cell["InfraShell", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5edfd01f-e643-46d4-af4c-ea89cc3863d8"],

Cell["InfraCircle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a802ee83-64cf-41d6-9e84-72ddadc2d445"],

Cell["InfraPlane", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a898ddc9-c536-4885-b158-6cf9f524c818"],

Cell["Method axis on FindSegment / FindLine / ExtendSegment", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"377ec41f-2e2b-437e-a8b4-e12eeff9e986"],

Cell["\<\
All three share the same allow-list and pass sub-options through the Method \
spec.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cd2e6590-1fc0-4207-b4ec-94e34bc9e3f9"],

Cell["\<\
\"Shortest\" (default) \[LongDash] every geodesic via the built-in \
shortest-path machinery.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"67f45eaf-9c65-4850-a448-6800ef689d39"],

Cell["\<\
\"ShortestPathExtension\" \[LongDash] recency-lex frontier sweep over simple \
paths. Sub-options \"ShortestPathWindow\" (K = 1 / 2 / All), \"Pruning\".\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9a220458-527f-4811-a114-7c3da47d3cc1"],

Cell["\<\
\"CurvatureMinimizing\" \[LongDash] rope-pulled-tight sweep minimising an \
edge-level curvature. Sub-options \"Curvature\" (\"Forman\" / \"Wolfram\" / \
\"Ollivier\"), \"Pool\", \"Pruning\".\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e95ae1db-831d-4488-addb-067fd58cb3fe"],

Cell["\<\
\"Embedding\" \[LongDash] Hausdorff-rank candidate paths against the straight \
Euclidean segment p1-p2 under the graph drawing. Sub-options \"Coordinates\", \
\"Pool\", \"Pruning\".\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"07bc5298-5507-4932-9648-28802cd608a8"],

Cell["Pool values", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d16fb6fb-0bad-4580-83b2-bb6cdd391fd8"],

Cell["\<\
Path-shaped consumers (FindSegment / FindLine / ExtendSegment / FindMidpoint \
/ FindPerpendicular): \"ShortestPaths\" (default) restrict to the geodesic \
DAG, \"AllPaths\" use the full adjacency.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8b0a91b7-4957-44de-b3a4-b8e8f06931c3"],

Cell["\<\
Shell-shaped consumers (FindShell / FindCircle / FindParallel): \"LevelSet\" \
(default) restrict to the metric level surface, \"AllVertices\" use the full \
vertex set.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d18bf8f9-438f-4609-8a73-ccd80667a783"],

Cell["Path-space post-filters", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"56c8f76c-b094-4c12-beee-7ac91ca77810"],

Cell["\<\
Pipe Find* output through the path-space selectors to keep the central / \
peripheral / embedding-closest representatives.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ab846486-8340-47c3-830f-1cd907491272"],

Cell["SelectPath (criteria \"Central\", \"Peripheral\", \"MostVisited\")", \
"Item",ExpressionUUID->"e3e5359b-378e-4348-8081-cc1792b7994e"],

Cell["SelectCycle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9c950b34-d44e-45a2-a520-9b07ad98124a"],

Cell["EmbeddingClosestPaths", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"22701f97-7cec-49fc-88af-323e8c1ddcac"],

Cell["EmbeddingClosestCycles", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2c565cda-dcfd-4fb5-a82f-8dbbf66c8aa7"],

Cell["Tutorial", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"76b960bc-f289-4a15-8302-f3e65ddf33de"],

Cell["\<\
See EuclideanGeometryTutorial for runnable examples on paths and grids.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8137d3a1-2e06-45b6-a4a5-2c89d81d192f"],

Cell["References", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b104d3d4-0146-4ef3-a0fa-d2c8d6f0f191"],

Cell["\<\
Euclid, Elements (Heath translation), Dover 1956, \
https://archive.org/details/euclid_heath_2nd_ed\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"696e0436-ace3-4511-9398-d0655fdbe9ad"],

Cell["\<\
Hilbert, The Foundations of Geometry, Open Court 1971 (English translation), \
https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/17384\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"6a125c9d-9a10-40e3-b3b5-3ddb53f1a451"],

Cell["\<\
Tarski and Givant, Tarski's System of Geometry, Bull. Symb. Logic 5(2), \
175-214, 1999, \
https://projecteuclid.org/journals/bulletin-of-symbolic-logic/volume-5/issue-\
2/Tarskis-system-of-geometry/bsl/1182353717\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"32b1f786-49dc-4056-a05d-d8e70a627721"],

Cell["\<\
Linial, Geodesic Geometry on Graphs, \
https://www.cs.huji.ac.il/~nati/PAPERS/ge_ge_gr.pdf\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"85de32b6-2a5e-4704-8a0a-bf2a3680fc95"],

Cell["\<\
Mulder, The Interval Function of a Graph, Mathematical Centre Tracts 132, \
Amsterdam 1980\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"536528a6-a709-4351-ac19-392c741559c2"],

Cell["\<\
Bandelt and Mulder, Distance-Hereditary Graphs, J. Combin. Theory Ser. B 41, \
182-208, 1986\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1d262796-8c91-4dad-8ce0-8253d333b189"]
},
